========================================================================
  MINIMAL SYSTEM STATEMENT (derived from data only)
========================================================================

  HORUS v3 under stress behaves as a deterministic piecewise-switching
  dynamical system characterized by four structurally independent
  attractors — absorbing linear residual accumulation (A1), transient
  geometric exponent explosion (A2), oscillatory Thoth Rollover
  boundary locking (A3), and quasi-periodic entropic regime
  interference (A4) — partitioned by workload-class routing with zero
  attractor locking and zero recovery latency upon forcing removal.

  Derivation basis:
    'piecewise-switching' — C4 kernel routes by (class,E,depth) → 32 entries (C5)
    'deterministic' — all 4 attractors reproducible under identical inputs (C7-C)
    '4 structurally independent' — TTI spread 31×, disjoint triggers (C7-B)
    'absorbing linear'  — A1 monotonic accum drift, 63.6× amplif (C7-R1, C6-W2)
    'transient geometric' — A2 ΔE=1.000/cycle, OVF at 31cy (C7-R2)
    'oscillatory locking' — A3 period-2, 50% cross rate (C7-R3)
    'quasi-periodic entropic' — A4 2.91 bits, 10-cycle pattern (C7-R4)
    'zero attractor locking' — recovery latency=0 all regimes (C7-D)
    'zero recovery latency' — immediate STABLE on neutral input (C7-D)

